

1. Selected my Operating System (OS): Windows 11
Step 1:Visited the official Windows 11 download page: (Windows 11 Download)(https://www.microsoft.com/software-download/windows11).
Step 2: I Followed on the on-screen instructions to download the Windows 11 installation media.
Step 3:I Installed Windows 11 by running the setup from the installation media.Then Followed the prompts to complete the installation.

FOR IDE
2. Installed a Text Editor or Integrated Development Environment (IDE): Visual Studio Code
Step 1:I visited the Visual Studio Code download page: Visual Studio Code Download(https://code.visualstudio.com/Download).
Step 2:Then Downloaded the installer for my operating system (Windows).
Step 3:Ran the installer and followed up the setup wizard to install Visual Studio Code.

 Set Up Version Control System: Git and GitHub
Step 1: Visited the Git download page: [Git Download](https://git-scm.com/downloads).
Step 2:Downloaded and installed Git by running the installer and following the setup instructions.
Step 3:Configured Git by opening a terminal and running:
Step 4:Created a GitHub account at [GitHub](https://github.com).
Step 5: Initialised a new Git repository

4. Install Necessary Programming Languages and Runtimes: Python
Step 1:Visited the Python download page: [Python Download](http://www.python.org).
Step 2:Then Download the latest version of Python and run the installer. Ensure you check the box to add Python to your PATH during installation.
Step 3:Verified the installation by opening a terminal and running.

5. Configure a Database: MySQL
Step 1:I visited the MySQL download page: [MySQL Download](https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/windows/installer/5.7.html).
Step 2:Download and run the MySQL Installer.
Step 3:Follow the setup wizard to install MySQL Server and configure it with the necessary root password.
Step 4: Verify the installation by logging into the MySQL command line:

